I'm not really sure what the best solution is. Lists are alot of work to maintain and it doesnt sound like there is much support for it. Although I think my guild would be in favor of it and happily help whoever was &quot;next&quot; up if such a system was made.<br>
<br>
Being a 80% european based guild we simply do not have the people needed to sit there 24/7 until ragefire spawns unlike some of the bigger guilds(well we probably could have one group hold it when the euros are sleeping, but would then need to rely on outside help for the actual kill, not an ideal situation). So for us whatever &quot;camptime&quot;(god I hate that word) we put in needs to be during the day.<br>
<br>
Which brings me to another point. Could we at least agree that you have to be physically present to claim that you are camping ragefire? For whatever reason(LD, urgent matter) there was noone claiming the solb camp earlier today for 30 mins+, so we moved in. <br>
<br>
Which then lead to some unnecessary debate when a cleric that had been gone for a long time logged in sitting on arch and wanted to reclaim camp. Thankfully we did reach an agreement though and we camped it to midnight CET, and they took over again from there. <br>
<br>
Anyway getting just one sprinkler in guild(for Cenne who shows up for 99% of our raids) is still our top priority, so we will continue to pop in during the day and see if people are camping him.<br>
<br>
Oh, and if anyone wants help taking out a ragefire just ask, if we are not doing anything we'll be happy to help.<br>
