</body><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uverbalsabre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Verbalsabre</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Mirth & Mayhem</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>59</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>3/30/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>5:11:04 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Proposal of Server Support...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ok I am sure this suggestion will go over like a qlead balloon but here it goes anyway. <br>
<br>
The idea, to my understanding, is to come together as a community to get as many rez sticks circulated as possible. In my opinion the focus should be to get one stick into every guild on the Rathe first and then to get the extra ones into each guild. <br>
<br>
Every guild gets to submit one cleric at a time to a list. The order would be as follows. <br>
<br>
* Guilds with no rez sticks go to top of the list. <br>
* Cleric must need ONLY Ragefire to complete quest. <br>
* Highest level charachter first. <br>
* If all the above is same for multiple clerics then the admins /ran or whatever to determine place on list. <br>
<br>
So we have Cleric's Moe, Larry and Cury <br>
<br>
Moe - Needs only Ragefire, guild has none, is 60th level<br>
Larry - Needs only Ragefire guild has one, is 60th level<br>
Curly - Needs Ragefire and ???, Guild has none, is 58th level. <br>
<br>
Moe goes first, Larry second, Curly cannot be on list because he needs more then Ragefire. When Curly does get to that point he would leapfrog over Larry because his guild has no rez sticks and Larry's does. <br>
<br>
Since each guild can only have one Cleric on list, and they must need only Ragefire to be on list, the list should be fairly short. <br>
<br>
Whichever cleric is highest on the list AND IS PRESENT when Ragefire spawns gets the loot. <br>
<br>
So Larry shows up by himself and sees Mo and his friends camping Ragefire, he hangs out with them and Ragefire pops. He helps anyway he can knowing that if Mo gets his it will move him to the top of the list. Mo gets his stick and he and his guild leave. <br>
<br>
Larry is now sitting at the camp by himself thinking &quot;Oh god please do not let anything spawn.&quot; It is his camp and therefore his responsibility to get a group in there. Nobody is available so he camps. He logs in the next day and walks back in to find Curly and friends camping Ragefire. It is Larry's camp still. Why would Curly let him waltz right in and loot something he had been camping? Because it will put him to the top of the list and make the camp his anytime he logs in. Larry hangs out for awhile, no ragefire, so he decides to go hunt orc pawns in EC for awhile. 2 minutes after he leaves Ragefire spawns. Does he get to zone back in and loot? No. Why? Because he was not the highest on the list present WHEN RAGEFIRE SPAWNED. Curly takes his piece and goes, Larry retains first right to the camp. <br>
<br>
Why this is a good idea?<br>
<br>
*** If you support this system there will come a point and time where you are #1 on the list. By supporting the system and defering to those that are higher on list you will create for yourself a situation where you will be guarenteed the camp any time you log in. <br>
<br>
*** You will help make sure that every guild on the Rathe has a stick which benefits us all. <br>
<br>
*** Every guild will have the opportunity to put another cleric on the list as soon as one completes his quest which will set up a natural rotation so that no guild dominates the spawn. <br>
<br>
*** Up and coming guilds will get to have an edge in the fact that their first cleric that needs a stick will go to the top of the list. <br>
<br>
And most important - Instead of a guild working together to help their cleric, it would be a server working together to help OUR clerics. <br>
<br>
If the camp was held by anyone that had not agreed to abide by this agreement then naturally there camp would have to be respected. <br>
<br>
DISCLAIMER - I am 46th level, have been for months. I play the game in a way that most do not relate to. I could care less if I ever level again or if I get my epic. Point is I do not know a lot about the high end game and therefore do not know how feasible this concept may be. I just want to throw my support behind any concept that creates a situation where the entire server is working towards a commen goal. Hell if this keeps up we are just going to be one gigantic guild before long <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As usual my view points are not just my own but are the official views of ogre wizards everywhere. <br>
<br>
&quot;2Cp....Some Noob....Some Guild&quot; <br>
