</table><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udaiaspiritlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daia Spiritlight</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Muse and Merriment</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>11</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>4/9/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>7:42:18 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/rbdignin/smdaialoth.jpg width=160 height=182></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Proposal of Server Support...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Coming late to the debate (as usual - I work a lot LOL).<br>
<br>
I am very happy to see folks discussing this idea *without* flaming.  I agree with the feelings of everyone who likes the idea of a server wide support system on this quest,and respect and understand those who point out legitimate issues of fairness (particularly for larger guilds with multiple clerics in need) about such a system.<br>
<br>
Like CoN, RoD and others have noted, there are guilds that simply have a dickens of a time mustering the numbers to keep this camp 24-7.  Mine is one of them.  We don't have the bodies.  Not for an up to 3 day continuous camp.  So does that mean we must do without? I guess for some that's a fine result.  But for those who are like me it would be nice if we could find a solution.  After all, we do pay the same $10 as everyone else even if we are online only 20 hours a week instead of 80, and many of us choose to not be in larger guilds who can produce dozens of continuous camp bodies, for many legitimate reasons.<br>
<br>
Without some larger cooperation, even though I just started the quest (damn that Lord Gimblox!) I may never see a res stick because my real life will not allow that type of time commitment unless I'm willing to face disciplinary charges with the Bar for neglecting my clients and Child Protective Services for neglecting my kids.  There is only so much vacation that one can take.  Putting it bluntly, even if I have the will (And believe me I do -- I'm the only 50+ cleric in my guild and life is rough when I face a mass-death situation), I do not have the way - not alone.<br>
<br>
So maybe a compromise? Those guilds in this thread that *do* support such a system for Ragefire, maybe *we* can come up with a list or rotation of sorts amongst ourselves?  After all, it's better than nothing.  Or is it? I'm sure I'm missing a lot of things that would be wrong with this type of idea.<br>
<br>
Thanks for listening.  One small fuss, in an otherwise quiet thread.  It drives me insane when folks directly or impliedly equate the inability or unwillingness to commit what are IMO unhealthy amounts of continuous gaming time in the manner that Verant rewards, for no damned good reason other than the fact that it can, with either motivation or desire to accomplish and succeed at quests in the game such as this one.  I wish folks wouldn't do that.</font><P><purple><b>Peace and Love and Hugs to All,<b><br>
<br>
<i>Lady Daia Spiritlight, High Priestess of Quellious<i><br>
